The paper introduces a new measure of similarity between graphs based on information theory, specifically the maximal number of source symbols per channel use that can be reliably sent over a channel with a confusion graph. This falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT) and graph theory (cs.DS, cs.DM). The paper also discusses applications to network information theory (cs.NI) and provides results related to graph cores and criticality (cs.SI).
